  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Land Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description & Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>1. Carry out land and engineering surveys, capping beam and pile cap setting out survey, traverse main and sub control lines</p><p>2. Carry out setting out of building grid lines before and during the construction stage</p><p>3. Prepare setting out data and pre calculation as per requirement</p><p>4. Carry out routine building alignment (horizontal and vertical) survey during the course of the project, perform field surveying to obtain data for base plans</p><p>5. Make accurate Pre-measurements and survey report for engineering to design</p><p>6. Ensure all coordinates on field alignment to match up to construction drawing</p><p>7. Any discrepancy between construction drawing and site condition to address immediately to Project team and Engineering</p><p>8. Make accurate post- measurements and survey report for as-built drawing</p><p>9. Preparation of data, collect and assess for design and construction works</p><p>10. Periodic check & verify Survey instruments</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>1. Diploma / Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent.</p><p>2. Minimum 10 years of working experience in land surveying and LTA.</p>",
